reviews_data.review_text: One of the absolute best places in Matthews.

You can't beat Carolina Beer Temple for their selection, service, genuine hospitality, or their ability to connect people in one space.

Best Belgian bar in the city, and has held that title for some time. Truly a beer temple.

In the same space, you have vendors for board and card games, mocktails, cocktails, beer, a THC vendor, ice cream, and more! Something truly for everyone!

Clean bathrooms as well, extra points there!
Exelent
Ok
Phillip was a great server.  The breakfast burrito was really good.  The menu has a good variety of brunch options.  Restaurant is clean and open
Always a great selection of beers and the bartenders are top notch!! The new space is huge with ice cream and an amazing cocktail bar in the back! Movie nights and weekly activities add to the fun!!🤩
So fun - great selection of beer.  A little loud, but it was really busy.  We look forward to coming back in.
Love that they are dog & kid friendly. It's a great space to meet up with my friends and enjoy drinks. Beer, wine, and liquor drinks from the back bar.

Let me just say this is a fantastic place to meet friends and family. The staff are amazing, super helpful and treat you like family.  We met some dear friends of ours here for dinner last week (one of whom is over 90 years old) and Asheley came over to our table to make sure they were comfortable and made some great recommendations based on their preferences which they really appreciated.  We’ve been coming here for years but it just keeps getting better. Make sure you check out the Two Scoops Creamery in the back for some amazing ice cream also!
Great area with lots of entertainment

Carolina Beer Temple at Ames Station is a huge departure from the old spot, and while I miss the cozy vibe of the original, this new location is absolutely massive, with tons of space and the cool addition of other shops inside. The beer selection is, as always, fantastic. However, there are a couple of things to note. First, I don't recommend sitting upstairs. It feels like it could be a good spot, but it's just not decorated well, completely loses all energy, and honestly feels like a sterile hotel conference area – not cozy at all. My other major gripe was when the super bright outdoor lights suddenly clicked on at 9 PM, completely shattering the evening ambiance and killing the vibe. If they could address the upstairs decor and adjust those outdoor lights, this place has even more potential.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the review and kind words. Regarding the exterior lighting, this is an issue we are aware of and it is under the control of our landlord. We are working to come up with some solutions as the lights are on a timer we do not control. As for the mezzanine - this is a work in progress. As we have only been open a little more than three months, we haven't been able to implement all of our plans yet and we have many plans for the mezzanine (and beyond) that will come together in the weeks and months ahead. Cheers!

reviews_data.review_text: Bartender was rude and the new space looks makeshift. Two scoops creamery is a fun plus but just be prepared for everybody’s kids running around barefoot. Insult to injury my mead was served room temp
Always a great place to visit for a brew and chill atmosphere. The added vending spaces, regular events, and monthly markets are great to check out, too
Great atmosphere-good beer-lots to do-and a dispensary!!!
Quite a variety! Pretty cool place!

This is such a cool place! Carolina beer Temple really knocked it out of the park. So many options here from beer to wine to food trucks to gaming to cocktails and even ice cream. It's a great place to hang out for a while or spend the whole day!
They have a great selection of craft beer. Wine for those who are not beer aficionados.

New location, same (and better) craft beer  selections. Largest location the brand has had and now with cocktails, game room, dispensary. Usually a rotating food truck on site. Plenty of indoor and outdoor seating!
Unbelievable selection of beer spanning all genres. Always something going on also. Gaming room, arcade and more.

I got weird with the Beard!
Best Temple and Clergy in Charlotte!
Love this place! Drinks are great and the over all vibe is dope deff recommend!!
Beer Temple is our favorite spot during work, after work, and on weekends. Beer selection is awesome and the vibe is the best in town.
New location is amazing. Love the versatility with the other vendors. You have the options for beer, liquor, indoor, or outdoor seating. Great place for friends to hang out.
The new location is excellent. It's in an area that is building a nice marketplace with a ton of future food options.
Great service and a knowledgeable staff. They are eager to explain all the types of beer they have. You may ask for a sample too. Good beer and good service.
I  went there to see my son wrestle. The place was extremely crowded because the ring was inside. Nevertheless, I had a great time.
Very large space with good selection of beer and liquor.   Even has a board game store in the middle so you can try out some new games while you drink!
Great service. Multiple bars. Lots of fun games. Great outdoor space. Plenty of inside space. Lots of local beers on tap. Serves wine and cocktails as well
Convenient parking and great selection. I miss the one in South Charlotte...
New location is awesome. Beers are WAY overpriced… gotta pay the rent somehow I guess 🤷🏻‍♂️
Solid cocktails, excellent beer options, check out the game store while you’re enjoying.
Great spot with lots of drink and seating options. Game store integrated in the building is nice.
Need bigger kids gaming area! Otherwise, great!
Great new location with beer bar and full bar.
We love the CBT with one small complaint, when sitting in the main downstairs area the lights in the mezzanine are SOOOO HARSH on your eyes! Please tilt them or dim them. Thanks

The new location is really nice.  Very open indoor/outdoor space with a full bar in the back and beer & wine offered at the front bar.  Great selection on tap or to take home. It will be even better when the pizza place and bakery open.

The new space is superb. The 2 bars, the meeting space upstairs, the CBD shop, the game store, pinball. What a great vibe! Loved the mocktail selection - I recommend a Red Rocket. Food truck space outside. Can't wait for the EV charger to be operational.
The new location has been a game changer and activates a new part of Matthews. Beer is solid, as always, but the constant rotation of food trucks and daily events makes this a destination.
Great place to meet new people. Friendly. Lots of space to move around.
The best beer in Matthews ! Love the temple .
The new space is amazing! Such a great idea to have four businesses under one roof. Love the rotating food truck selection too!
The new location is great, there is so much space indoor and outdoor. They have a good selection of drinks and they often have events or food trucks there.
Love the new place! More room, amd more beer!
Fantastic & beautiful place! Awesome owners and workers. THE best hangout anywhere!
Very friendly. Space is clean, and the beer selection is fabulous.  New location and it is awesome!

The new space is wonderful!  Very open with indoor and outdoor seating.  Expanded wine selection with something for all tastes.  It was great seeing Save July play yesterday as well.  I've been trying to get them to do more day gigs.  Thanks!

The best Bar in Matthews and one of the best Bars in the Charlotte Metro area!
Great beer selection, plenty of events going on, friendly bartenders and a sense of helping the local community!
Always on point!
Great Beer
As an Iowa fan Ames Street is not my go to but I am sure it will still be great
Great beer selection.
Good beer spot in downtown Matthews. I believe it is moving locations
My wife and I love the Beer Temple — especially on a Sunday afternoon, having a beer and bringing the kids to kill time.  It’s just a really cool place and awesome beers.
Cool place, good selection, great service.
Small cute neighborhood bar .. we are planning to move this area! It was so great to experience the downtown area...
Beer pub in the town of Matthews. Seems like a nice soccer place but we watched a college football game. Varied different kinds of beer
Love our little place.  A.great gathering spot for friends family and sports lovers!!
Knowledgeable staff, great beer on tap, and a fantastic selection in the bottle shop area.
Excellent service ! The burgers are amazing .

I was greeted and assisted immediately upon arrival at the temple. The only difficulty is narrowing down a final purchase from the offerings on hand. Luckily there is an illuminated menu board and I was able to get a pour of one of the latest and greatest from a local hero on tap. I was initially hesitant about the new location but it is impossible to deny the character of their current building. I don't regret the effort put forth to find free parking, and I look forward to finishing up the bounty I took home.
Great place to have the perfect beer! Love it!
Large diverse tap and craft can bottle selection. Indoor and outdoor seating.
Always super friendly and beers are fresh because they don’t have a ton of room.  Parking can be a challenge but it’s got a cool vibe and we are lucky to have them in Matthews.

My go-to for all craft beer needs. 26 beers on draft from all over, including some of their own. They even allow you to grab singles and drink on-site. Solid, diverse wine list. Crazy huge NA menu. Tons of events every week.  What more could you ask for?
Lovely little bar
Friendly staff, great beer & a neat outdoor area.
If you are looking to check out some of charlotte's finest brewery's offerings, this will be a good place to check out

The running club on Tuesday evenings is so much fun. After the run, you can relax and enjoy a refreshing beer. It’s a perfect combination of fitness and socializing, with a friendly community atmosphere. Highly recommended

This place is awesome!  Old school bottle shop with an excellent selection of bottles and I think about 15 drafts?  You can tell a lot of thought was put in to the beer selection.  Very, very impressive.  Bartenders were very helpful and friendly.  Awesome bier garten to hang out and watch people in a perfect location in downtown Matthews.  There is only 1 drawback I noticed and it's a big one.  I live in Huntersville and it's a little bit of a drive for me." :) I can't wait to go back.  Thanks to my buddy Delan for recommending this place.  5 Stars!
Best bar in Matthews

First time here. Came to see live music. Great beer selection, nice outdoor space and super friendly staff. No food but we got an awesome pizza delivered from a restaurant nearby. Nice space for live music, which is why we came here.
Good place to get a pint and listen to live music. Large beer selection.  Lots of food nearby. Kid and pet friendly.
Great selection, friendly staff, and clean place.

The beer temple is absolutely wonderful. I had my first beer here when I turned 21. They always have a great selection, and a place to sit with your friends. The atmosphere is welcoming and lighthearted. If you are looking for a place to hang out, you should be going to the beer temple. Cheers.
Wow, many different brands of vitamin B.
Great team, amazing service,  very good choice of beer. Snacks only.
Quickly a favorite stop. Great drafts.  Amazing selection of beers to take home. Good use of an old post office.  Seating indoor or outdoors. Quaint bar.
So many great beers! Cool atmosphere!
Great selection of beers and nice atmosphere.

Very cool place! The beer selection is good, and the beer itself was excellent! There is a good truck out back and plenty of other food options close by. The outdoor area is great and a wonderful way to hang out for the day!
Love that Carolina Beer Temple prioritizes local breweries and other small breweries - it's a great place to hang if you have the time!

Hands down, the best beer shop in Matthews.

Carolina Beer Temple offers some of the best variety of beers in the Charlotte area. Their tap selection is solid & consistently changing. They carry the usual Charlotte based breweries but seem to focus on the highly rated ones. They carry excellent out of state offerings, too. Some of the highlights include Equilibrium, Trillium, & Xul.

The building is the old Post Office. This definitely adds a unique character.

The environment fits the setting, which equals a perfect spot to play games & enjoy great beer.

Carolina Beer Temple is worth stopping at for a few beers & then to take some to go.

Simply the best place to spend a few hours to unwind.  Matt the manager is very personable and always connect with everyone who comes in. Actually the entire staff does same. You feel truly appreciated and connected.  If you have seen the sitcom Cheers this is that kind of place.  Could not be any better.  Cheers.
Small selection of hard to find beer at reasonable prices
Very small but absolute top shelf assortment of beers including some seriously rare imports. Everything is available in single bottles. Extremely friendly and helpful staff.
I love a place that offers a small pour so you can try a variety!! The beer minister, Matt, was amazing! In love with the atmosphere, we will definitely be back!
Killer hangs to be had every time I visit.
Great place, Ken and Sam were great and excellent customer service.
Staff are very welcoming
Nice selection of taps and to-go options. I'll be returning next time I'm in the area!

Very relaxed atmosphere with some TVs for sports and soft music so talking isn't an issue (thank you for that!) If you like hard cider the Blackberry cider was phenomenal and I would absolutely recommend it! Cool place, we had never been there before and we ended up enjoying it quite a bit!
They have some very interesting flavors of beer - all categories covered - Amber , Lager, IPA , sour .. and a cool outdoors to enjoy on a sunny day
These people know their beer!
Great craft beer, more choices than one could ever want! Matt is the man to go to!!! He is full of beer knowledge and will definitely help you find the right beer for your taste! Great place!!!!
Great place, great atmosphere good selection of craft beers
Fun little local pub. Indoor and outdoor seating available. Wide variety of microbrew options. Glad we stopped in and we will be back!
Great craft beer
My favorite store!!!
Cool atmosphere, nice outside seating. Variety of choices. Good $1/scoop snacks
Cool spot with great beer and good vibe.
This place is awesome!!  Lots of good beers for the beer lover and lots of great wine for the wine connoisseur!  The place is a historic post office (as an added bonus)!
Great spot for a relaxing evening (with kids or dogs as well!)
very interesting place, fine spot for families
Best watering hole in Matthews!

Cool spot in Matthews. A wide variety of good tasting beers on the menu, plenty of seating outside and there was a band there for entertainment. I’m a big fan of the Matthews area and this bar fits into the vibe very well.
Had a great time. Loved the wine. My friend loved her beer. The band and the outdoor seating area were awesome. Great Saturday afternoon
Excellent beer selection, great people both drinking and behind the bar. If you like beer you need to come here.
Nice place to relax outdoors. They have plenty of choices to drink there or take home.
If you love beer you will love this place!

This is one of my favorite go-to places.  Awesome beer and wine selection, snacks for my hungry toddler (and me), lovely outdoor space, phenomenal service.  Shout out to Matt who now knows my drink order by heart 😄 oh, and the place is super dog friendly and family friendly as long as you are responsible human/pet parents who don’t leave your ankle biters/mutts unattended.  My son loves sitting outside and watching the train go by. Keep rocking, Beer Temple!
Great beer selection, location and service!
Awesome bar! Location is amazing for sitting outside and enjoying downtown Matthews. Fantastic variety of beers
Good variety of beer. Very busy, so you can wait to be attended for a while and you might get bored or forgotten.
Awesome staff and selection!

Great spot to grab a drink. plenty of options for every taste. There is plenty of seating all around the building and they almost always have a fantastic food truck to help soak up all the beers you will try.
Fun place love sitting outside!
The outdoor space is great! Spent a few hours here with the kiddos playing on the lawn. Good beer in a great spot!
Great beer selection

I was here with our 30 something grandkids and their children for a short gathering. Each lives about 20 miles from it in different directions. Food truck delivers inside. Excellent selection of beers.
Great place and great beer and awesome people
Best set of taps in town along with being a bottle shop! Staff is great! Local regulars are what make this place awesome. Have been a patron for ten years now. Never gets old!
Great place with great atmosphere

If you visit Charlotte. Matthews is not a far trip with tons of local eaterys and shops. But a must stop for any Beer fan is here.
Tons of rotating brews from all over. Tons of stocked unique brews to take home and growlers.
Tiny small "garage" atmosphere, they don't serve food but partner with some amazing food trucks you can bring the food inside. Great outdoor area to enjoy the town and meet friends. Always a weekly stop for me.
Good if not great.
Love this spot!  Great beer and a great staff that are knowledgeable, friendly,  and approachable.  A++ 5 Stars Definitely Recommend
My sister, mom and I had a great experience!
Really enjoy going here.  Nice little speakeasy.
Good beer very warm Good service

Great place for a beer with friends! The run club meets every Tuesday at 6:30pm. 30-40 runners show up normally. It's a great group and a great place to meet. Carolina Beer Temple has been a wonderful host!
Great local spot with a huge assortment of beer. Awesome vibe and great people!

Such a lovely local place to go get a beer and boy do they have many options. The people are friendly and the environment is nice too. Even better downtown Matthews in general has such a nice feel. Check this place out and the game store next door!

Great staff! With a wonderful beer selection for drafts and craft cans.

A host location for Charlotte FC's fan group Mint City Collective.
Amazing beer selection and fantastic atmosphere. Take home beer selection is also on point.
Great beer
Great place to get some great beer!
My husband and I have been here several times. We love the beers they have on tap and it is a great atmosphere sitting inside or outside.
Great selection of craft beer and chill vibe. Would definitely come back
Great energy
This is a nice spot overall. Kind of small on the inside, but there's a lot of seating outside. Not great if it is raining though. Lots of drinks to choose from.
Great place to stop in for a beer, great selection and very friendly staff. I real like the outside with the Adirondack chairs.
Great Stafff.Great Location

Pulled into this Gem while waiting to meet some friends for dinner. I did not regret it.  Sam was Awesome. Wonderful personality, immediately made me feel welcome and had great feedback. I found a few IPA's to add to my list and even tried a few new one's. My only suggestion is that they add a flight to the beer menu.
Cool setting. Family and dog friendly. Mobile food on site

Nice and cozy spot, only reason why I gave it 4stars was because I assumed there was a bigger selection to take home (only 2 medium size fridges to choose from) . It's more of a sit down place, but I will come back just for sitting down!

I love that there is constantly new local brews and weekly events.  They keep their Facebook page very up to date with the fun events like board gaming, different food trucks, featured brews and tastings, etc.

Great beer - lots of taps, rotating frequently to highlight beer from across the state. They offer free Wi-Fi if you like to mix up your work environment. There are several outdoor tables with umbrellas on all sides of the building. Dogs are welcome and you can get water for them. Right next door to Seaboard so if you're with friends preferring wine it's a great spot for both. Doing great with wearing and requiring masks.
Loved it!.....very cool
Great service, friendly staff and laid back atmosphere. People seemed to be really enjoying soccer while I was there. Good selection of craft beers and really nice outdoor seating area.
Great atmosphere
Amazing beer selection. The team behind the bar know their stuff and can give anyone a good recommendation.
This place is the bomb! The bartenders are always great. Thursday tap takeover and Fridays they have an IPA special and all the restaurants close will deliver !
Fun place to have a beer or two.

Great casual place to hang out! Beers on tap are switched out daily and there is a great variety! Small seating area inside bar but many seating areas outside. Most people there purchased outside food like pizza and brought it there to eat at the picnic tables. Very kid friendly and live music played when we went on a Saturday evening. Will be going again soon!
Good experience. Matt is very personable. Thoroughly enjoyed.
Relaxed vibe, great location, friendly staff. Perfect place for watching CLT FC .
Friendly staff! Great selection of craft beer! I loved the atmosphere!
Team is great at advising people to the best choice.
Awesome spot!!! Extremely friendly staff as well as the customers with their pets 😊

Went here for the first time today because they were having an amateur chili cook off. So figured no better time to try them out. I tried the sour beer that’s currently on tap and it was awesome. The whole place is small and quaint and I love that. Customer service was good and quick. I love how Matthews has come alive over the years and this place fits right in
Lovely and cosy place to get off the beaten track brews, and a very friendly bar keep! No food though, just munchies by the cup. Good for stopping by for a casual pint before moving on to eats!
Great place for craft beers. They always have a large selection of new beers on tap. Good location in downtown Matthews within walking distance to restaurants and other fun places to visit.
Great selection on tap and cans to take home (only 4 packs)
Pretty good but not as good as Seaboard. They have a nice selection. We particularly liked the green drink!
Great beer and wine selections
Nice service!
Nice place for an after work drink.  Great beer selection and the staff was very friendly and helpful with making my selections.
I enjoy the astroturf outside area when I want to get a drink, and if I'm on the go, their bottle shop always has the good stuff
Carolina Beer Temple // Run Club Tuesdays changed my life. Cheers!

Carolina Beer Temple is one of the coolest beer and wine bars I've ever been inside. It's in an old Post Office in Matthews, NC, and, of course, the beer is great along with great outdoor seating. The owner Rob is super cool and is very welcoming. Great place!!!
Great beer options and very cool atmosphere!

Out of all of the places I have been to this is one of the few that gets a 1 star and it is sad. I try to respect all people but when you walk in and immediately have political beliefs pushed on you just to order a beer. It's not worth it. So many other amazing places close by.
I like it! Very relaxing and great beer! Staff are very friendly and patient to explain the extensive beer menu. Love the downtown Matthews area!
Great service
Nice place to hang out and chill, good food nearby and a good outdoor area to eat it at
Cool spot.  Great beers and great service!

Starting going here when it was temple mojo. Still a casual place to grab a good beer. Check the tap list before you go as we stopped in last time and there were only a handful of beers that weren't sours from a prior tap takeover.
Great place for a beer and to relax!
Always a good beer selection and the outdoor seating are is killer!
Great beer choices! Any place that both my husband and I are happy with is perfect given he's a stout man and I'm an IPA boy
reviews_data.owner_answer: Glad we could find something for both of y’all! Thanks for coming through!

reviews_data.review_text: What's not to like?
Very chill place for a drink.
Great people, super nice, lots of options (even nonalcoholic) and a run club on Tuesday nights
Great selection, friendly bar staff, and not too crowded or rowdy. Nice place to hang out and enjoy downtown Matthews.
We really enjoyed stopping here for some cold beer. Very friendly and made us feel welcome. We'll be back!
Good beer good patio, perfect for kids and pets or just friends. Hot sun request cold beer 🍺
Great outdoor space,huge selection!
My favorite spot to grab beer for the house and always has something from Europe I've not tried yet. They also have a love for De Ranke beers which will always keep me coming back.
Different kind of feel.
Cool little stop in Matthews. Not much for ambiance, but decent beer selection on tap and a lot of take and go options.

Located in the heart of downtown matthews. Surrounded by a lot of different other places to eat, shop and hang out. A wide variety of different beers on tap. Indoor, outdoor, and back patio area. Family-friendly and pet friendly. Awesome place definitely worth checking out.

2nd time here. Visited last Sun. Not crowded, nice families with cute kids, chill music, unpretentious. Got a shady table and had a few IPAs with the hubs and the pup. Beer is great, as well as the service.
Best local beer selection and knowledge.  Love the outdoor spaces.
Really good beer and really good beer tenders.
Great staff and selection, cool outdoor space, I'll be back
They have a great outdoor space for those of us who are not quite ready to sit inside. They always have a great number of options.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Appreciate the review! We hope to add even more outdoor seating this summer!

reviews_data.review_text: Had a great experience!
Awesome local taproom and bottle shop.  Great indoor and outdoor venue and knowledgeable staff.  Always a great selection.
Love the Beer Temple.
Awesome tap house, definitely the best in Charlotte.
Solid place
Always amazing beers and incredible staff.
Awesome place to get a drink after a long run. Speaking of running..come join us on Tuesday 6:45pm for Carolina Beer Temple's Run Club.

This place has gone down hill. The service was awful last time I went, which is discouraging because I used to enjoy going. No way I would pay a cent to this business based on my last visit. One star is one star too many.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We’re sorry you had a bad experience last time in. If you don’t mind, please reach out to us via scott@carolinabeertemple.com or right here to let us know what went wrong and how we can provide a better experience.

reviews_data.review_text: Mojo was fantastic as always
Lots of delicious beers with a good variety of styles to choose from. Friendly staff. Wish it were closer to Gastonia. 😩
Great craft beers, good people and awesome outdoor space in Matthews’ town center. Great atmosphere and always somebody you know strolling by.

The place to go for some local craft brews in Matthews! These guys always have a fantastic selection both on tap and in their bottle section! They also do Growler fills which is rare to find so bring your growlers and come away with some great beer and good memories!
Wide variety of beer from all over the world available at very reasonable prices

They are open however you can't browse inside the store or break up packs of beer due to covid so it's pretty limited. For those who want to have a draft onside you can do so in their garden/patio area.
I came here after "Seaboard Brewing, Taproom, & Wine Bar" - over there was really bad and I was upset... But here guys know what they doing and awesome service. I like this place. Thank you guys.
Great beer and nice relaxing location. Plenty of outdoor seating to safely social distance.
Great beer selections and reasonably prices. Love Beer temple!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks! Great to see you the other day, Cheers!

reviews_data.review_text: Carolina Beer Temple is amazing!!! They helped us pick beers based on our likes and what we love! they are very knowledgeable and helpful! I would highly recommend.I will be back in person to hang out!
Great place
Friendly staff, large variety, fun environment
The craft beer here is the best in town!

Drafts are rotated quite frequently. There is usually a brewery night where they will have several drafts available from the brewery of the night. Nice craft beer along the walls to shop. Beer in the cooler has a few singles that you can open at the store (keep in mind there is a upcharge if you do). They don't serve food, but you can bring in your own or order takeout and have it delivered to the store.
Tons of great beers and great people. I love coming to the game night on Mondays
Nice hole in the wall to find extravagant craft beers. Price is a little high but worth the stop.
Great place to play a board game and grab some beer!
Amanda is the best BEERista ever!!!!
Great selection of beers both on tap and take home bottles. Bar tenders are friendly and helpful. Owners really support the growing community.

Love the atmosphere here, great staff always on hand to give background on what's on tap, surprise samples, and even some unexpected snacks! We always appreciate the welcoming vibe and friendly bartenders. Highly recommend if you want to try excellent local beers and seasonal drinks as well as rare canned/bottled beers from around the country.
Nice, but too small of selection of cans and bottles.
Plenty to drink from!
Friendly and knowledgeable staff. Cute atmosphere and great music! Definitely worth the trip if you're in Matthews!
Great beer selection and staff is second to none!
Great beer selection. Friendly people. Would go again.
Great rotating tap.  Bottled selection has shrunk it seems.  But I think I like the flow of it better now.
Always a fun spot for beer and great conversation!!
Fantastic beer selection! Staff is very accommodating. Relaxing atmosphere at a great location.
Great selection of wine and craft beer

Great selection, great staff. They answer your questions and work with you to find that perfect drink. They rotate the selection of beers on tap quite frequently so you can always find something new to try.
Okay selection, prices are significantly higher than other places. But I guess if you want to support local we just have to deal with it.

I love this place.  The staff is great.  Beer selection is always on point.  Seating is comfortable.  You can always find interesting beers in their bottle selection.  They have regular tap takeovers and events that are fun.
Wonderful service. A lot of choices! Great place to enjoy a drink!!!
They have beer.  All you need to know.
Great people. Good times.
Great selection.
Great selection of draft and extensive bottle shop. Encourages takeout food from neighborhood shops.
Friendly great place to have a beer
Very nice place to visit.
Still amazing beer knowledge and selection with focus on Belgian beets and styles
Friendly atmosphere and knowledgeable staff.  I felt comfortable letting the bartender choosing beers based on my likes. Jordan was great.
Wonderful selection of Beers. Staff can be a bit "prickly"..... #BeerSnobs
Love it
I wish there was more of a selection
One of our favorite date places. Delicious local beers, local delivery for food, and a variety of games to play. Staff always friendly and helpful. Can buy a large variety of beer to take home.
Great spot for a drink and chat with friends. Excellent customer service!
Great laid back place to grab a beer. They have a great selection of canned and bottled beer for purchase as well.No kitchen on site but you can order from local places and have it delivered.

reviews_data.review_text: One of the absolute best places in Matthews.

You can't beat Carolina Beer Temple for their selection, service, genuine hospitality, or their ability to connect people in one space.

Best Belgian bar in the city, and has held that title for some time. Truly a beer temple.

In the same space, you have vendors for board and card games, mocktails, cocktails, beer, a THC vendor, ice cream, and more! Something truly for everyone!

Clean bathrooms as well, extra points there!
Exelent
Ok
Phillip was a great server.  The breakfast burrito was really good.  The menu has a good variety of brunch options.  Restaurant is clean and open
Always a great selection of beers and the bartenders are top notch!! The new space is huge with ice cream and an amazing cocktail bar in the back! Movie nights and weekly activities add to the fun!!🤩
So fun - great selection of beer.  A little loud, but it was really busy.  We look forward to coming back in.
Love that they are dog & kid friendly. It's a great space to meet up with my friends and enjoy drinks. Beer, wine, and liquor drinks from the back bar.

Let me just say this is a fantastic place to meet friends and family. The staff are amazing, super helpful and treat you like family.  We met some dear friends of ours here for dinner last week (one of whom is over 90 years old) and Asheley came over to our table to make sure they were comfortable and made some great recommendations based on their preferences which they really appreciated.  We’ve been coming here for years but it just keeps getting better. Make sure you check out the Two Scoops Creamery in the back for some amazing ice cream also!
Great area with lots of entertainment

Carolina Beer Temple at Ames Station is a huge departure from the old spot, and while I miss the cozy vibe of the original, this new location is absolutely massive, with tons of space and the cool addition of other shops inside. The beer selection is, as always, fantastic. However, there are a couple of things to note. First, I don't recommend sitting upstairs. It feels like it could be a good spot, but it's just not decorated well, completely loses all energy, and honestly feels like a sterile hotel conference area – not cozy at all. My other major gripe was when the super bright outdoor lights suddenly clicked on at 9 PM, completely shattering the evening ambiance and killing the vibe. If they could address the upstairs decor and adjust those outdoor lights, this place has even more potential.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the review and kind words. Regarding the exterior lighting, this is an issue we are aware of and it is under the control of our landlord. We are working to come up with some solutions as the lights are on a timer we do not control. As for the mezzanine - this is a work in progress. As we have only been open a little more than three months, we haven't been able to implement all of our plans yet and we have many plans for the mezzanine (and beyond) that will come together in the weeks and months ahead. Cheers!

reviews_data.review_text: Bartender was rude and the new space looks makeshift. Two scoops creamery is a fun plus but just be prepared for everybody’s kids running around barefoot. Insult to injury my mead was served room temp
Always a great place to visit for a brew and chill atmosphere. The added vending spaces, regular events, and monthly markets are great to check out, too
Great atmosphere-good beer-lots to do-and a dispensary!!!
Quite a variety! Pretty cool place!

This is such a cool place! Carolina beer Temple really knocked it out of the park. So many options here from beer to wine to food trucks to gaming to cocktails and even ice cream. It's a great place to hang out for a while or spend the whole day!
They have a great selection of craft beer. Wine for those who are not beer aficionados.

New location, same (and better) craft beer  selections. Largest location the brand has had and now with cocktails, game room, dispensary. Usually a rotating food truck on site. Plenty of indoor and outdoor seating!
Unbelievable selection of beer spanning all genres. Always something going on also. Gaming room, arcade and more.

I got weird with the Beard!
Best Temple and Clergy in Charlotte!
Love this place! Drinks are great and the over all vibe is dope deff recommend!!
Beer Temple is our favorite spot during work, after work, and on weekends. Beer selection is awesome and the vibe is the best in town.
New location is amazing. Love the versatility with the other vendors. You have the options for beer, liquor, indoor, or outdoor seating. Great place for friends to hang out.
The new location is excellent. It's in an area that is building a nice marketplace with a ton of future food options.
Great service and a knowledgeable staff. They are eager to explain all the types of beer they have. You may ask for a sample too. Good beer and good service.
I  went there to see my son wrestle. The place was extremely crowded because the ring was inside. Nevertheless, I had a great time.
Very large space with good selection of beer and liquor.   Even has a board game store in the middle so you can try out some new games while you drink!
Great service. Multiple bars. Lots of fun games. Great outdoor space. Plenty of inside space. Lots of local beers on tap. Serves wine and cocktails as well
Convenient parking and great selection. I miss the one in South Charlotte...
New location is awesome. Beers are WAY overpriced… gotta pay the rent somehow I guess 🤷🏻‍♂️
Solid cocktails, excellent beer options, check out the game store while you’re enjoying.
Great spot with lots of drink and seating options. Game store integrated in the building is nice.
Need bigger kids gaming area! Otherwise, great!
Great new location with beer bar and full bar.
We love the CBT with one small complaint, when sitting in the main downstairs area the lights in the mezzanine are SOOOO HARSH on your eyes! Please tilt them or dim them. Thanks

The new location is really nice.  Very open indoor/outdoor space with a full bar in the back and beer & wine offered at the front bar.  Great selection on tap or to take home. It will be even better when the pizza place and bakery open.

The new space is superb. The 2 bars, the meeting space upstairs, the CBD shop, the game store, pinball. What a great vibe! Loved the mocktail selection - I recommend a Red Rocket. Food truck space outside. Can't wait for the EV charger to be operational.
The new location has been a game changer and activates a new part of Matthews. Beer is solid, as always, but the constant rotation of food trucks and daily events makes this a destination.
Great place to meet new people. Friendly. Lots of space to move around.
The best beer in Matthews ! Love the temple .
The new space is amazing! Such a great idea to have four businesses under one roof. Love the rotating food truck selection too!
The new location is great, there is so much space indoor and outdoor. They have a good selection of drinks and they often have events or food trucks there.
Love the new place! More room, amd more beer!
Fantastic & beautiful place! Awesome owners and workers. THE best hangout anywhere!
Very friendly. Space is clean, and the beer selection is fabulous.  New location and it is awesome!

The new space is wonderful!  Very open with indoor and outdoor seating.  Expanded wine selection with something for all tastes.  It was great seeing Save July play yesterday as well.  I've been trying to get them to do more day gigs.  Thanks!

The best Bar in Matthews and one of the best Bars in the Charlotte Metro area!
Great beer selection, plenty of events going on, friendly bartenders and a sense of helping the local community!
Always on point!
Great Beer
As an Iowa fan Ames Street is not my go to but I am sure it will still be great
Great beer selection.
Good beer spot in downtown Matthews. I believe it is moving locations
My wife and I love the Beer Temple — especially on a Sunday afternoon, having a beer and bringing the kids to kill time.  It’s just a really cool place and awesome beers.
Cool place, good selection, great service.
Small cute neighborhood bar .. we are planning to move this area! It was so great to experience the downtown area...
Beer pub in the town of Matthews. Seems like a nice soccer place but we watched a college football game. Varied different kinds of beer
Love our little place.  A.great gathering spot for friends family and sports lovers!!
Knowledgeable staff, great beer on tap, and a fantastic selection in the bottle shop area.
Excellent service ! The burgers are amazing .

I was greeted and assisted immediately upon arrival at the temple. The only difficulty is narrowing down a final purchase from the offerings on hand. Luckily there is an illuminated menu board and I was able to get a pour of one of the latest and greatest from a local hero on tap. I was initially hesitant about the new location but it is impossible to deny the character of their current building. I don't regret the effort put forth to find free parking, and I look forward to finishing up the bounty I took home.
Great place to have the perfect beer! Love it!
Large diverse tap and craft can bottle selection. Indoor and outdoor seating.
Always super friendly and beers are fresh because they don’t have a ton of room.  Parking can be a challenge but it’s got a cool vibe and we are lucky to have them in Matthews.

My go-to for all craft beer needs. 26 beers on draft from all over, including some of their own. They even allow you to grab singles and drink on-site. Solid, diverse wine list. Crazy huge NA menu. Tons of events every week.  What more could you ask for?
Lovely little bar
Friendly staff, great beer & a neat outdoor area.
If you are looking to check out some of charlotte's finest brewery's offerings, this will be a good place to check out

The running club on Tuesday evenings is so much fun. After the run, you can relax and enjoy a refreshing beer. It’s a perfect combination of fitness and socializing, with a friendly community atmosphere. Highly recommended

This place is awesome!  Old school bottle shop with an excellent selection of bottles and I think about 15 drafts?  You can tell a lot of thought was put in to the beer selection.  Very, very impressive.  Bartenders were very helpful and friendly.  Awesome bier garten to hang out and watch people in a perfect location in downtown Matthews.  There is only 1 drawback I noticed and it's a big one.  I live in Huntersville and it's a little bit of a drive for me." :) I can't wait to go back.  Thanks to my buddy Delan for recommending this place.  5 Stars!
Best bar in Matthews

First time here. Came to see live music. Great beer selection, nice outdoor space and super friendly staff. No food but we got an awesome pizza delivered from a restaurant nearby. Nice space for live music, which is why we came here.
Good place to get a pint and listen to live music. Large beer selection.  Lots of food nearby. Kid and pet friendly.
Great selection, friendly staff, and clean place.

The beer temple is absolutely wonderful. I had my first beer here when I turned 21. They always have a great selection, and a place to sit with your friends. The atmosphere is welcoming and lighthearted. If you are looking for a place to hang out, you should be going to the beer temple. Cheers.
Wow, many different brands of vitamin B.
Great team, amazing service,  very good choice of beer. Snacks only.
Quickly a favorite stop. Great drafts.  Amazing selection of beers to take home. Good use of an old post office.  Seating indoor or outdoors. Quaint bar.
So many great beers! Cool atmosphere!
Great selection of beers and nice atmosphere.

Very cool place! The beer selection is good, and the beer itself was excellent! There is a good truck out back and plenty of other food options close by. The outdoor area is great and a wonderful way to hang out for the day!
Love that Carolina Beer Temple prioritizes local breweries and other small breweries - it's a great place to hang if you have the time!

Hands down, the best beer shop in Matthews.

Carolina Beer Temple offers some of the best variety of beers in the Charlotte area. Their tap selection is solid & consistently changing. They carry the usual Charlotte based breweries but seem to focus on the highly rated ones. They carry excellent out of state offerings, too. Some of the highlights include Equilibrium, Trillium, & Xul.

The building is the old Post Office. This definitely adds a unique character.

The environment fits the setting, which equals a perfect spot to play games & enjoy great beer.

Carolina Beer Temple is worth stopping at for a few beers & then to take some to go.

Simply the best place to spend a few hours to unwind.  Matt the manager is very personable and always connect with everyone who comes in. Actually the entire staff does same. You feel truly appreciated and connected.  If you have seen the sitcom Cheers this is that kind of place.  Could not be any better.  Cheers.
Small selection of hard to find beer at reasonable prices
Very small but absolute top shelf assortment of beers including some seriously rare imports. Everything is available in single bottles. Extremely friendly and helpful staff.
I love a place that offers a small pour so you can try a variety!! The beer minister, Matt, was amazing! In love with the atmosphere, we will definitely be back!
Killer hangs to be had every time I visit.
Great place, Ken and Sam were great and excellent customer service.
Staff are very welcoming
Nice selection of taps and to-go options. I'll be returning next time I'm in the area!

Very relaxed atmosphere with some TVs for sports and soft music so talking isn't an issue (thank you for that!) If you like hard cider the Blackberry cider was phenomenal and I would absolutely recommend it! Cool place, we had never been there before and we ended up enjoying it quite a bit!
They have some very interesting flavors of beer - all categories covered - Amber , Lager, IPA , sour .. and a cool outdoors to enjoy on a sunny day
These people know their beer!
Great craft beer, more choices than one could ever want! Matt is the man to go to!!! He is full of beer knowledge and will definitely help you find the right beer for your taste! Great place!!!!
Great place, great atmosphere good selection of craft beers
Fun little local pub. Indoor and outdoor seating available. Wide variety of microbrew options. Glad we stopped in and we will be back!
Great craft beer
My favorite store!!!
Cool atmosphere, nice outside seating. Variety of choices. Good $1/scoop snacks
Cool spot with great beer and good vibe.
This place is awesome!!  Lots of good beers for the beer lover and lots of great wine for the wine connoisseur!  The place is a historic post office (as an added bonus)!
Great spot for a relaxing evening (with kids or dogs as well!)
very interesting place, fine spot for families
Best watering hole in Matthews!

Cool spot in Matthews. A wide variety of good tasting beers on the menu, plenty of seating outside and there was a band there for entertainment. I’m a big fan of the Matthews area and this bar fits into the vibe very well.
Had a great time. Loved the wine. My friend loved her beer. The band and the outdoor seating area were awesome. Great Saturday afternoon
Excellent beer selection, great people both drinking and behind the bar. If you like beer you need to come here.
Nice place to relax outdoors. They have plenty of choices to drink there or take home.
If you love beer you will love this place!

This is one of my favorite go-to places.  Awesome beer and wine selection, snacks for my hungry toddler (and me), lovely outdoor space, phenomenal service.  Shout out to Matt who now knows my drink order by heart 😄 oh, and the place is super dog friendly and family friendly as long as you are responsible human/pet parents who don’t leave your ankle biters/mutts unattended.  My son loves sitting outside and watching the train go by. Keep rocking, Beer Temple!
Great beer selection, location and service!
Awesome bar! Location is amazing for sitting outside and enjoying downtown Matthews. Fantastic variety of beers
Good variety of beer. Very busy, so you can wait to be attended for a while and you might get bored or forgotten.
Awesome staff and selection!

Great spot to grab a drink. plenty of options for every taste. There is plenty of seating all around the building and they almost always have a fantastic food truck to help soak up all the beers you will try.
Fun place love sitting outside!
The outdoor space is great! Spent a few hours here with the kiddos playing on the lawn. Good beer in a great spot!
Great beer selection

I was here with our 30 something grandkids and their children for a short gathering. Each lives about 20 miles from it in different directions. Food truck delivers inside. Excellent selection of beers.
Great place and great beer and awesome people
Best set of taps in town along with being a bottle shop! Staff is great! Local regulars are what make this place awesome. Have been a patron for ten years now. Never gets old!
Great place with great atmosphere

If you visit Charlotte. Matthews is not a far trip with tons of local eaterys and shops. But a must stop for any Beer fan is here.
Tons of rotating brews from all over. Tons of stocked unique brews to take home and growlers.
Tiny small "garage" atmosphere, they don't serve food but partner with some amazing food trucks you can bring the food inside. Great outdoor area to enjoy the town and meet friends. Always a weekly stop for me.
Good if not great.
Love this spot!  Great beer and a great staff that are knowledgeable, friendly,  and approachable.  A++ 5 Stars Definitely Recommend
My sister, mom and I had a great experience!
Really enjoy going here.  Nice little speakeasy.
Good beer very warm Good service

Great place for a beer with friends! The run club meets every Tuesday at 6:30pm. 30-40 runners show up normally. It's a great group and a great place to meet. Carolina Beer Temple has been a wonderful host!
Great local spot with a huge assortment of beer. Awesome vibe and great people!

Such a lovely local place to go get a beer and boy do they have many options. The people are friendly and the environment is nice too. Even better downtown Matthews in general has such a nice feel. Check this place out and the game store next door!

Great staff! With a wonderful beer selection for drafts and craft cans.

A host location for Charlotte FC's fan group Mint City Collective.
Amazing beer selection and fantastic atmosphere. Take home beer selection is also on point.
Great beer
Great place to get some great beer!
My husband and I have been here several times. We love the beers they have on tap and it is a great atmosphere sitting inside or outside.
Great selection of craft beer and chill vibe. Would definitely come back
Great energy
This is a nice spot overall. Kind of small on the inside, but there's a lot of seating outside. Not great if it is raining though. Lots of drinks to choose from.
Great place to stop in for a beer, great selection and very friendly staff. I real like the outside with the Adirondack chairs.
Great Stafff.Great Location

Pulled into this Gem while waiting to meet some friends for dinner. I did not regret it.  Sam was Awesome. Wonderful personality, immediately made me feel welcome and had great feedback. I found a few IPA's to add to my list and even tried a few new one's. My only suggestion is that they add a flight to the beer menu.
Cool setting. Family and dog friendly. Mobile food on site

Nice and cozy spot, only reason why I gave it 4stars was because I assumed there was a bigger selection to take home (only 2 medium size fridges to choose from) . It's more of a sit down place, but I will come back just for sitting down!

I love that there is constantly new local brews and weekly events.  They keep their Facebook page very up to date with the fun events like board gaming, different food trucks, featured brews and tastings, etc.

Great beer - lots of taps, rotating frequently to highlight beer from across the state. They offer free Wi-Fi if you like to mix up your work environment. There are several outdoor tables with umbrellas on all sides of the building. Dogs are welcome and you can get water for them. Right next door to Seaboard so if you're with friends preferring wine it's a great spot for both. Doing great with wearing and requiring masks.
Loved it!.....very cool
Great service, friendly staff and laid back atmosphere. People seemed to be really enjoying soccer while I was there. Good selection of craft beers and really nice outdoor seating area.
Great atmosphere
Amazing beer selection. The team behind the bar know their stuff and can give anyone a good recommendation.

Fun place to have a beer or two.

Most people there purchased outside food like pizza and brought it there to eat at the picnic tables. Very kid friendly and live music played when we went on a Saturday evening. Will be going again soon!
Good experience. Matt is very personable. Thoroughly enjoyed.
Relaxed vibe, great location, friendly staff. Perfect place for watching CLT FC .
Friendly staff! Great selection of craft beer! I loved the atmosphere!
Team is great at advising people to the best choice.
Awesome spot!!! Extremely friendly staff as well as the customers with their pets 😊

Went here for the first time today because they were having an amateur chili cook off. So figured no better time to try them out. I tried the sour beer that’s currently on tap and it was awesome. The whole place is small and quaint and I love that. Customer service was good and quick. I love how Matthews has come alive over the years and this place fits right in
Lovely and cosy place to get off the beaten track brews, and a very friendly bar keep! No food though, just munchies by the cup. Good for stopping by for a casual pint before moving on to eats!
Great place for craft beers. They always have a large selection of new beers on tap. Good location in downtown Matthews within walking distance to restaurants and other fun places to visit.

Great beer and wine selections
Nice service!
Nice place for an after work drink.  Great beer selection and the staff was very friendly and helpful with making my selections.
I enjoy the astroturf outside area when I want to get a drink, and if I'm on the go, their bottle shop always has the good stuff
Carolina Beer Temple // Run Club Tuesdays changed my life. Cheers!

Carolina Beer Temple is one of the coolest beer and wine bars I've ever been inside. It's in an old Post Office in Matthews, NC, and, of course, the beer is great along with great outdoor seating. The owner Rob is super cool and is very welcoming. Great place!!!
Great beer options and very cool atmosphere!

Out of all of the places I have been to this is one of the few that gets a 1 star and it is sad. I try to respect all people but when you walk in and immediately have political beliefs pushed on you just to order a beer. It's not worth it. So many other amazing places close by.
I like it! Very relaxing and great beer! Staff are very friendly and patient to explain the extensive beer menu. Love the downtown Matthews area!
Great service
Nice place to hang out and chill, good food nearby and a good outdoor area to eat it at
Cool spot.  Great beers and great service!

Starting going here when it was temple mojo. Still a casual place to grab a good beer. Check the tap list before you go as we stopped in last time and there were only a handful of beers that weren't sours from a prior tap takeover.
Great place for a beer and to relax!
Always a good beer selection and the outdoor seating are is killer!
Great beer choices! Any place that both my husband and I are happy with is perfect given he's a stout man and I'm an IPA boy
reviews_data.owner_answer: Glad we could find something for both of y’all! Thanks for coming through!

Great selection, friendly bar staff, and not too crowded or rowdy. Nice place to hang out and enjoy downtown Matthews.
We really enjoyed stopping here for some cold beer. Very friendly and made us feel welcome. We'll be back!
Good beer good patio, perfect for kids and pets or just friends. Hot sun request cold beer 🍺
Great outdoor space,huge selection!
My favorite spot to grab beer for the house and always has something from Europe I've not tried yet. They also have a love for De Ranke beers which will always keep me coming back.
Different kind of feel.
Cool little stop in Matthews. Not much for ambiance, but decent beer selection on tap and a lot of take and go options.

Located in the heart of downtown matthews. Surrounded by a lot of different other places to eat, shop and hang out. A wide variety of different beers on tap. Indoor, outdoor, and back patio area. Family-friendly and pet friendly. Awesome place definitely worth checking out.

2nd time here. Visited last Sun. Not crowded, nice families with cute kids, chill music, unpretentious. Got a shady table and had a few IPAs with the hubs and the pup. Beer is great, as well as the service.
Best local beer selection and knowledge.  Love the outdoor spaces.
Really good beer and really good beer tenders.
Great staff and selection, cool outdoor space, I'll be back

reviews_data.owner_answer: Appreciate the review! We hope to add even more outdoor seating this summer!

Awesome local taproom and bottle shop.  Great indoor and outdoor venue and knowledgeable staff.  Always a great selection.
Love the Beer Temple.
Awesome tap house, definitely the best in Charlotte.
Solid place

Awesome place to get a drink after a long run. Speaking of running..come join us on Tuesday 6:45pm for Carolina Beer Temple's Run Club.

This place has gone down hill. The service was awful last time I went, which is discouraging because I used to enjoy going. No way I would pay a cent to this business based on my last visit. One star is one star too many.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We’re sorry you had a bad experience last time in. If you don’t mind, please reach out to us via scott@carolinabeertemple.com or right here to let us know what went wrong and how we can provide a better experience.

reviews_data.review_text: Mojo was fantastic as always
Lots of delicious beers with a good variety of styles to choose from. Friendly staff. Wish it were closer to Gastonia. 😩
Great craft beers, good people and awesome outdoor space in Matthews’ town center. Great atmosphere and always somebody you know strolling by.

The place to go for some local craft brews in Matthews! These guys always have a fantastic selection both on tap and in their bottle section! They also do Growler fills which is rare to find so bring your growlers and come away with some great beer and good memories!
Wide variety of beer from all over the world available at very reasonable prices

They are open however you can't browse inside the store or break up packs of beer due to covid so it's pretty limited. For those who want to have a draft onside you can do so in their garden/patio area.
I came here after "Seaboard Brewing, Taproom, & Wine Bar" - over there was really bad and I was upset... But here guys know what they doing and awesome service. I like this place. Thank you guys.
Great beer and nice relaxing location. Plenty of outdoor seating to safely social distance.
Great beer selections and reasonably prices. Love Beer temple!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks! Great to see you the other day, Cheers!

Nice hole in the wall to find extravagant craft beers. Price is a little high but worth the stop.

Amanda is the best BEERista ever!!!!
Great selection of beers both on tap and take home bottles. Bar tenders are friendly and helpful. Owners really support the growing community.
